<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-13T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115L98/2</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Rome</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tredwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-13T21:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 14, 1
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>British Consul, Cagliari, Sardinia, reports: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>Captain <persName>McDonough</persName> and nine men, crew
                                        ex-American sailor [<hi rend="italic">schooner</hi>] <hi rend="italic">Lyman M. Law</hi>, New York, reported
                                        destroyed by submarine yesterday morning, have just landed
                                        here. Master begs you for assistance.</p>
                                    <p rend="right">Pernis, British Consul</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <p>Am making investigation. May leave for Cagliari to-morrow.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tredwell</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>